{%- comment -%}
  templates/product.quickview.liquid
  Alternate product template — only used by the Sections Rendering API.
  URL: /products/{handle}?view=quickview&sections=product-quickview

  Shopify requires an alternate template to exist before the
  &sections= parameter will return JSON instead of raw HTML.
  This template intentionally renders nothing — the only output
  that matters is the section JSON payload returned by the API.

  How it works:
    1. product-card.js → initQuickView() fetches:
         /products/{handle}?view=quickview&sections=product-quickview
    2. Shopify renders this template (blank), then bundles the
       rendered output of sections/product-quickview.liquid under
       the key "product-quickview" in the JSON response.
    3. JS extracts data["product-quickview"] and injects it into
       the .quickview-modal__body element.

  Do NOT add {% section 'product-quickview' %} here — that would
  double-render the section (once via this include, once via the
  sections API wrapper), producing duplicate HTML in the response.
{%- endcomment -%}
